})} />

<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How much does microwave repair cost?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Our diagnostic fee is $89, applied toward the repair once you approve the work. Most microwave repairs run between $100 and $250. A door switch, thermal fuse, or turntable motor replacement is toward the lower end. Magnetron replacement is the higher end of microwave repair, we'll give you an honest repair vs. replace assessment before recommending it, since a new mid-range microwave sometimes costs less."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Which areas of Southern California do you cover?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "All five counties: Los Angeles, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside. We dispatch from 8 service territories, West Hollywood (HQ), Los Angeles, Beverly Hills, Pasadena, Thousand Oaks, Irvine, Rancho Cucamonga, and Temecula, so the technician on your call is coming from the closest one. Same-day is our standard."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Why is microwave repair dangerous to attempt yourself?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Microwaves contain a high-voltage capacitor that stores a charge of 2,000 volts or more, and it retains that charge even after the microwave is unplugged. Touching it without properly discharging it first can be fatal. This is not an exaggeration and not a liability disclaimer. It's the reason microwave repair belongs with a trained technician who knows the correct discharge procedure. Our technicians discharge the capacitor as the first step before any internal work."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "My microwave is sparking or arcing inside, is it safe to use?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "No. Stop using it immediately. Sparking inside a microwave can indicate a failing waveguide cover coated with food residue, a damaged stirrer, or, more seriously, a failing magnetron. Using a microwave that's arcing can damage the magnetron and the cavity walls, turning a minor repair into a major one. In some cases arcing is caused by something as simple as a dirty waveguide cover, but it needs to be diagnosed before the unit is operated again."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "My microwave runs but doesn't heat, what's usually wrong?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Three most common causes: a failed high-voltage diode (most frequent, the diode converts power to the magnetron and when it fails the magnetron gets no usable voltage), a failed magnetron itself, or a failed high-voltage capacitor. Less commonly, a failed door switch can also prevent heating without showing other symptoms. Our technicians carry high-voltage diodes for the major brands, this is the most common microwave repair we do."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "When does it make sense to repair vs replace a microwave?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "It depends on the type of microwave and the repair cost. A $79 countertop microwave is almost never worth repairing, replacement is cheaper. An over-the-range microwave built into cabinetry or a drawer microwave installed under a counter is a different calculation: replacement requires removing cabinetry or cutting a new hole, which can cost $200–$500 in labor. Built-in and over-the-range units are almost always worth repairing unless the magnetron has failed on a basic model. We give you this assessment before writing any repair order."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do you repair over-the-range and built-in microwaves?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. Over-the-range and built-in units are more involved than countertop units, the microwave often has to be partially removed from its mounting to access internal components. We work on these regularly and come prepared with the correct mounting knowledge for the brands common across SoCal kitchens: GE, KitchenAid, Samsung, LG, Whirlpool, Bosch, and Wolf."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What does the 90-day warranty cover on microwave repairs?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Every microwave repair we complete carries a 90-day warranty on both parts and labor. If the same issue returns within that window, we come back at no charge. That's in writing before we leave."
      }
    }
  ]
})} />

