    <h2 class="section-title">Specific microwave problems covered in depth</h2>
    <p class="lead">Each sub-service walks through the diagnostic logic, parts cost, and field-tested honest opinion for the most common microwave failure modes. High-voltage components inside a microwave hold lethal charge even when unplugged, these pages explain why we don't recommend DIY on the magnetron side.</p>
    <div class="problems-grid">
      <a href="/services/microwave-repair/not-heating/" class="problem-card" style="display:block; text-decoration:none; color:inherit;">
        <h3>Microwave Not Heating →</h3>
        <p>Runs but produces no heat. HV diode is the most common cause. Magnetron, capacitor, transformer diagnostic. Panasonic NN-SN/NN-SD inverter models follow a different repair tree.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/services/microwave-repair/no-power/" class="problem-card" style="display:block; text-decoration:none; color:inherit;">
        <h3>Microwave No Power / Dead →</h3>
        <p>Display dead, no response. About 30% resolve at the $89 diagnostic with GFCI/outlet check. Internal line fuse, door interlocks, thermal fuse, control board.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/services/microwave-repair/plate-not-rotating/" class="problem-card" style="display:block; text-decoration:none; color:inherit;">
        <h3>Plate Not Rotating →</h3>
        <p>Microwave still heats. Drive coupler is the cheapest fix ($129 typical). Turntable motor, support roller, control board signal. Lowest-urgency microwave failure mode.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/services/microwave-repair/sparking-arcing/" class="problem-card" style="display:block; text-decoration:none; color:inherit;">
        <h3>Sparking or Arcing Inside →</h3>
        <p>Stop using immediately. Mica waveguide cover (often called "wax paper" by customers) is the leading cause. Brown/black burn = replace cover. White discoloration = wipe and assess.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
